{{Short description|Body of water in the Sea of Japan}}
[[File:Sea Of Genkai up20060427.jpg|thumb|Genkai Sea in 2005]]
The {{nihongo|'''Genkai Sea'''|玄界灘|Genkai-nada}} <ref>{{cite book|last=Loyd Batten|first=Bruce|title= Gateway to Japan:Hakata in War And Peace, 500-1300|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|pages=38}}</ref> is a {{ill|Body of water|en|Body of water|qid=Q15324|lt=Body of water}} that comprises the southwestern tip of the {{ill|Sea of Japan|en|Sea of Japan|qid=Q27092|lt=Sea of Japan}} and borders the northern coasts of {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|en|Fukuoka Prefecture|qid=Q123258|lt=Fukuoka}} and {{ill|Saga Prefecture|en|Saga Prefecture|qid=Q160420|lt=Saga}} prefectures.

